1
00:01:28,950 --> 00:01:32,020
[Silent Honor]

2
00:01:32,370 --> 00:01:34,850
[Episode 14]

3
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:37,820
Deputy Chief,

4
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:39,460
that's true.

5
00:01:43,130 --> 00:01:44,630
But Chief Zhou also said

6
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:47,180
that this shipment of military supplies

7
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:48,450
is a top priority.

8
00:01:49,810 --> 00:01:51,610
I'm in a difficult position too.

9
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:58,539
Have these ships departed yet?

10
00:01:58,539 --> 00:01:59,920
The last batch just left.

11
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:02,260
Don't worry.
As soon as the ships return to port,

12
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:04,790
I'll immediately
allocate them for your use.

13
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,880
But you'll need to

14
00:02:09,410 --> 00:02:10,870
put in a good word for me

15
00:02:11,180 --> 00:02:12,180
and ask the Chief

16
00:02:12,270 --> 00:02:13,500
for a two-day extension.

17
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,500
Then I can free up ships for Vietnam.

18
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:16,530
Right?

19
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:17,490
Fine.

20
00:02:18,470 --> 00:02:20,070
Notify me as soon as your ships dock.

21
00:02:20,070 --> 00:02:22,070
I need to assess the situation first

22
00:02:22,070 --> 00:02:23,800
and then figure out a solution.

23
00:02:26,690 --> 00:02:27,380
Sir.

24
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:30,000
Prepare the Southeast combat zone maps.

25
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:30,600
Yes, sir.

26
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:44,200
Sir, have you received some news?

27
00:02:46,430 --> 00:02:47,720
Zhou Zhirou has arranged
for the Fourth Department

28
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:50,250
to transport
military supplies to Zhoushan.

29
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,320
I'm not sure what supplies exactly,

30
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,320
but it's urgent.

31
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:54,680
Do you think

32
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,020
it's related to the recent

33
00:02:57,020 --> 00:02:58,780
secret meeting
at the Hsinchu Air Force Base?

34
00:02:58,780 --> 00:02:59,640
It's possible.

35
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:02,020
Zhoushan has always been

36
00:03:02,020 --> 00:03:04,020
the maritime shield for East China.

37
00:03:04,820 --> 00:03:06,280
If the two are connected,

38
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,150
then we can confirm

39
00:03:09,150 --> 00:03:12,150
it's not an Air Force operation
from southwest China.

40
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:17,230
The day after tomorrow, I'll go check
the ships returning from Zhoushan.

41
00:03:17,230 --> 00:03:18,160
Come with me,

42
00:03:19,060 --> 00:03:20,690
and let's see if we can discover anything.

43
00:03:20,690 --> 00:03:21,220
Alright.

44
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:28,720
[Keelung Middle School]

45
00:03:38,380 --> 00:03:39,910
I, your servant Li Mi, respectfully
submit this memorial.

46
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:41,560
I have suffered misfortune

47
00:03:41,590 --> 00:03:44,100
[Seal of Ministry of Defense]

48
00:03:41,810 --> 00:03:43,360
and early calamity,

49
00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:45,079
being only 6 months old

50
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:46,870
when my kind father passed away.

51
00:03:46,870 --> 00:03:48,310
At the age of 4,

52
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,000
my uncle forced my mother into remarriage.

53
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,360
Grandmother Liu pitied my weakness

54
00:03:52,470 --> 00:03:53,870
and raised me herself.

55
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,620
Timeless literature

56
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,329
must excel in expressing emotion.

57
00:03:58,810 --> 00:03:59,740
Although "Memorial to the Throne"

58
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:01,470
was Li Mi's petition to Emperor Wu of Jin,

59
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:02,900
every word and sentence

60
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,480
expresses deep emotion.

61
00:04:05,030 --> 00:04:07,000
So when writing essays, students,

62
00:04:07,690 --> 00:04:09,620
you must not focus only on objects.

63
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,120
Mr. Gu.

64
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,040
Hello, Mr. Gu.

65
00:04:24,540 --> 00:04:25,350
Mr. Gu.

66
00:04:26,010 --> 00:04:27,960
Mr. Zhuang, well said!

67
00:04:28,220 --> 00:04:30,620
Indeed, every word is filled with emotion.

68
00:04:31,270 --> 00:04:32,200
You're too kind.

69
00:04:32,370 --> 00:04:33,230
I'm flattered.

70
00:04:34,010 --> 00:04:35,670
Standing alone and isolated,

71
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,920
with only my shadow for company.

72
00:04:38,510 --> 00:04:39,360
Mr. Zhuang,

73
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,630
you're not alone in Taiwan.

74
00:04:42,870 --> 00:04:45,720
In life, I am ready to give my life;

75
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:49,810
in death, I will still
repay Your Majesty's kindness.

76
00:04:49,810 --> 00:04:53,610
Unable to suppress my loyal feelings
like those of a humble servant,

77
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:56,480
I earnestly submit
this memorial to Your Majesty.

78
00:04:58,330 --> 00:05:01,530
Li Mi's "Memorial to the Throne"
is beautifully written,

79
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:03,880
moving people with emotion.

80
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:04,420
Yes.

81
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,320
Moving people with emotion.

82
00:05:06,690 --> 00:05:07,550
How wonderful.

83
00:05:17,010 --> 00:05:18,190
Four months ago,

84
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:22,560
I was still teaching
Chinese literature here.

85
00:05:25,090 --> 00:05:26,650
That peaceful life

86
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:30,130
is something I truly miss.

87
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:32,590
Leader.

88
00:05:33,510 --> 00:05:35,510
When I first reported to the bureau,

89
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:37,270
everyone was talking about

90
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,690
how Mr. Gu cracked
the Guangming News case

91
00:05:39,690 --> 00:05:41,940
and busted
the Communist spy den in Keelung.

92
00:05:41,940 --> 00:05:45,140
Everyone from the President
to the Director praised you.

93
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:46,690
I became an agent...

94
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,250
I joined this line of work

95
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:51,330
because I was afraid of being bullied

96
00:05:51,330 --> 00:05:52,810
and needed to make a living.

97
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:53,770
I never thought

98
00:05:54,550 --> 00:05:56,610
someone could make
such a career out of it like you did.

99
00:05:56,610 --> 00:05:58,530
So I went to the personnel department

100
00:05:58,530 --> 00:06:00,910
and insisted on
being transferred under your command.

101
00:06:00,910 --> 00:06:02,780
And you actually selected me.

102
00:06:04,780 --> 00:06:06,380
For the Guangming News case,

103
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:08,250
the President gave the Director

104
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:10,310
a reward of 300,000 Taiwan dollars.

105
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:12,390
300,000!

106
00:06:14,550 --> 00:06:16,950
Director Ye only
makes 600 dollars a month.

107
00:06:19,430 --> 00:06:21,580
You're quite well-informed.

108
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:25,480
I heard it from others.

109
00:06:27,410 --> 00:06:29,400
Do you think 600 is too little?

110
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:31,890
Well, 600 for me

111
00:06:31,890 --> 00:06:33,360
would be too much.

112
00:06:33,690 --> 00:06:34,830
600 isn't much,

113
00:06:36,290 --> 00:06:38,640
but it certainly isn't little either.

114
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:40,620
But you

115
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:44,870
are right to have
great ambitions and ideals.

116
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:48,360
Because once you solve major cases,

117
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:51,090
you'll naturally
receive substantial rewards.

118
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,930
Otherwise, would you
follow Director Ye's example?

119
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:56,890
Not enough money
and unable to solve cases,

120
00:06:56,890 --> 00:07:00,620
resorting to roadside kidnappings.

121
00:07:01,670 --> 00:07:02,820
Yes, Leader.

122
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:05,930
Mere cleverness won't achieve greatness.

123
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:08,500
From now on, if you tell me to go east,

124
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,100
I won't take half a step west.

125
00:07:27,370 --> 00:07:28,770
Director Ma, you certainly don't waste

126
00:07:28,770 --> 00:07:30,500
the Navy's shipping capacity.

127
00:07:31,540 --> 00:07:33,750
The ships aren't fully
loaded on return voyages anyway.

128
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,280
It would be a shame to waste the tonnage.

129
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,740
Loading some local specialties

130
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:37,920
can help make a bit of freight money.

131
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:40,020
The Fourth Department knows
how to calculate profits.

132
00:07:40,020 --> 00:07:41,600
We have no choice, Deputy Chief.

133
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,800
Money is needed everywhere these days.

134
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:49,800
That Liberty Ship looks good.

135
00:07:54,170 --> 00:07:56,010
Deputy Chief, that one

136
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,610
needs to assemble more millitary equipment

137
00:07:57,610 --> 00:07:58,730
to Zhoushan.

138
00:07:58,870 --> 00:08:00,770
Let's go and check others.

139
00:08:01,010 --> 00:08:02,790
You can use another ship
to transport the military supplies.

140
00:08:02,790 --> 00:08:03,790
Leave this to me.

141
00:08:03,820 --> 00:08:04,770
Let's go check.

142
00:08:10,540 --> 00:08:13,750
Great achievements start with small steps.

143
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:18,390
I think

144
00:08:19,550 --> 00:08:21,010
with your qualifications

145
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:23,830
you'd be quite suitable
for infiltration work

146
00:08:23,830 --> 00:08:25,070
here in Taiwan.

147
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:28,500
Infiltration?

148
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:30,780
Yes.

149
00:08:33,030 --> 00:08:35,030
Based on the information we have,

150
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:39,400
Lin Yiliang, the boss
of Sanrong Trading in Keelung,

151
00:08:39,860 --> 00:08:42,320
is most likely
to be Zhang Hao's accomplice.

152
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,580
So I plan to arrange you

153
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,870
to infiltrate

154
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,290
as Mr. Zhuang Achen.

155
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:52,040
Help me find out
Lin Yiliang's background.

156
00:08:53,370 --> 00:08:54,340
But Leader,

157
00:08:54,810 --> 00:08:57,440
I've never done infiltration work before.

158
00:08:58,630 --> 00:08:59,650
I'm afraid

159
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:01,890
I might ruin your master plan.

160
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:03,170
Come on.

161
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,170
Don't be such a coward.

162
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:05,700
Sit down.

163
00:09:10,190 --> 00:09:11,320
You, Weng Lianwang,

164
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,640
are on your first infiltration mission.

165
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,910
But that Mr. Zhuang Achen

166
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,480
is also escaping for the first time.

167
00:09:19,770 --> 00:09:21,230
Both of you are panicking.

168
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,810
What's the difference?

169
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:23,550
Right?

170
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:26,400
Besides, I'll personally guide you.

171
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:28,190
I brought you here today

172
00:09:28,350 --> 00:09:29,870
to get you familiar with

173
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,830
the Keelung Middle School campus.

174
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:35,890
These are the materials
prepared for you in advance.

175
00:09:35,890 --> 00:09:37,940
Memorize them as soon as possible.

176
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:39,590
From now on,

177
00:09:40,070 --> 00:09:41,870
you are no longer Weng Lianwang.

178
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,320
You are Mr. Zhuang Achen.

179
00:09:45,330 --> 00:09:47,170
If there's anything you don't understand,

180
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:48,670
you can go to the prison

181
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:51,080
and have a chat
with the real Zhuang Achen.

182
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,300
To go to Vietnam to withdraw troops,

183
00:10:01,730 --> 00:10:03,960
if we use smaller ships,
we'll need to send more of them.

184
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,640
It would be troublesome to coordinate.

185
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:08,440
So I'd prefer to send
the Liberty Ship if possible.

186
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:10,770
After all, this is a diplomatic mission.

187
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:13,290
If the ships are too shabby,
they don't look

188
00:10:13,290 --> 00:10:14,750
very presentable in front of the French.

189
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:18,680
Right, the President always prioritizes
international impression.

190
00:10:19,570 --> 00:10:21,830
Deputy Chief, please take another look.

191
00:10:25,620 --> 00:10:27,160
I'll go down to check the cabin.

192
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:28,280
Please, after you.

193
00:10:47,970 --> 00:10:48,770
Mr. Zhuang.

194
00:10:56,670 --> 00:10:57,240
Leader.

195
00:10:57,770 --> 00:10:58,700
What did you say?

196
00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:00,590
Have you lost your mind?

197
00:11:01,830 --> 00:11:03,550
I'm memorizing my lecture notes.

198
00:11:03,550 --> 00:11:05,860
Mr. Gu, just tell me what's on your mind.

199
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,530
Alright.

200
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:12,480
I won't bother you
with memorizing the lecture notes.

201
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:24,790
You're using this oil drum for water?

202
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:27,050
You bet. It's genuinely made in the U.S..

203
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:29,050
Look, it says right here.

204
00:11:29,190 --> 00:11:32,380
U.S. Air Force exclusive oil drum.

205
00:11:32,780 --> 00:11:34,600
Much lighter than our old iron buckets.

206
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,650
They just unloaded in Zhoushan.

207
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:37,580
So I grabbed an empty one for water.

208
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:39,380
Pretty handy.

209
00:11:50,630 --> 00:11:52,000
It seems Zhou Zhirou

210
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:54,130
has transported jet fuel to Zhoushan.

211
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:57,220
Judging from the shipping records,

212
00:11:57,940 --> 00:11:59,380
the quantity is substantial.

213
00:11:59,380 --> 00:12:00,420
We can confirm

214
00:12:01,150 --> 00:12:02,100
that Zhoushan

215
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:05,090
is coordinating with Air Force operations.

216
00:12:05,580 --> 00:12:06,930
Could it possibly be

217
00:12:07,470 --> 00:12:09,880
a joint naval, ground,

218
00:12:10,490 --> 00:12:11,760
and air combat operation?

219
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:13,090
Since November,

220
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:17,240
they've been
reinforcing the Zhoushan Islands.

221
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:19,440
And Chiang Kai-shek has explicitly

222
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:21,970
outlined an offensive-defensive strategy.

223
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:22,940
He ordered the Air Force to intensify

224
00:12:22,940 --> 00:12:24,710
attacks on maritime and coastal areas.

225
00:12:24,710 --> 00:12:25,760
Plus, recently,

226
00:12:26,670 --> 00:12:30,270
Zhou Zhirou has been frequently
attending meetings in Hsinchu.

227
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,050
And the level of secrecy

228
00:12:32,980 --> 00:12:34,220
is so strict.

229
00:12:34,820 --> 00:12:36,170
I think it's more likely

230
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:39,820
an unilateral operation of the air force.

231
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:41,210
Zhoushan...

232
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,980
If it is Zhoushan,

233
00:12:45,370 --> 00:12:46,200
it should be

234
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:49,180
in the southeast direction.

235
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:52,850
The southeastern islands
now have only one remaining airport,

236
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:55,430
which is the Dinghai Airport in Zhoushan.

237
00:12:55,580 --> 00:12:56,200
Sir,

238
00:12:56,950 --> 00:13:00,460
where do you think
they're most likely to bomb?

239
00:13:09,150 --> 00:13:10,070
In my view,

240
00:13:10,690 --> 00:13:12,610
to achieve your objectives,

241
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:14,850
the bombing priorities should,

242
00:13:14,850 --> 00:13:16,710
in addition to military targets,

243
00:13:17,140 --> 00:13:18,540
also focus on

244
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:20,530
Shanghai's industrial facilities,

245
00:13:20,530 --> 00:13:22,560
especially power plants, shipyards,

246
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:24,560
water treatment plants, and docks.

247
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,240
This way,

248
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:28,630
we can eliminate
the Communist Army's war potential

249
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,500
to ensure Zhoushan's safety,

250
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:32,010
and destroy
the confidence of Shanghai citizens

251
00:13:32,010 --> 00:13:35,210
and even the entire nation's
trust in the Communist Army.

252
00:13:35,490 --> 00:13:36,260
However,

253
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:39,750
strategic bombing has limited precision

254
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,260
and will affect innocent people.

255
00:13:43,570 --> 00:13:47,270
Shanghai in our hands

256
00:13:47,330 --> 00:13:48,880
is truly Shanghai.

257
00:13:50,670 --> 00:13:52,130
In the Communists' hands,

258
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:54,080
it's just Communist territory.

259
00:13:55,030 --> 00:13:58,600
I'm assigning this task to you.

260
00:14:00,020 --> 00:14:01,290
Maintain secrecy.

261
00:14:02,410 --> 00:14:03,960
We can't guarantee

262
00:14:04,990 --> 00:14:08,240
there aren't Communist spies in our ranks.

263
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:10,300
Rest assured, President.

264
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:13,600
I plan to select elite personnel
from the Second Department

265
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:15,630
specifically for security measures.

266
00:14:15,630 --> 00:14:16,810
I can guarantee you

267
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:18,910
that besides the Air Force,

268
00:14:18,910 --> 00:14:21,230
no one will know the complete plan.

269
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:24,890
Even Director Ma
who's responsible for transportation

270
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:28,080
won't know
what the fuel shipped to Zhoushan

271
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:29,590
is actually for.

272
