[Ningbo]

273
00:15:03,630 --> 00:15:04,380
[Shanghai]

274
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:05,980
Shanghai?

275
00:15:12,130 --> 00:15:13,960
Bombing Ningbo
would be the most convenient.

276
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:16,220
But that's Chiang Kai-shek's hometown.

277
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:18,250
Bombing Hangzhou is also an option.

278
00:15:18,630 --> 00:15:21,160
But in terms of impact
and destructive power,

279
00:15:21,650 --> 00:15:24,310
Ningbo and Hangzhou
can't compare to Shanghai.

280
00:15:24,550 --> 00:15:27,060
Plus, with the recent months
of naval blockade

281
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:28,320
and economic embargo,

282
00:15:30,130 --> 00:15:30,820
I believe

283
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:33,110
the Air Force's plan

284
00:15:33,150 --> 00:15:34,850
is to use Zhoushan as a springboard

285
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:35,920
and forward base

286
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:38,520
to stockpile aviation supplies in advance,

287
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:39,890
and to wait for the right moment

288
00:15:39,890 --> 00:15:40,910
to bomb Shanghai.

289
00:15:48,990 --> 00:15:51,740
Shanghai and Zhoushan
are very close to each other.

290
00:15:51,740 --> 00:15:54,400
The Air Force can
carry out maintenance nearby,

291
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:56,700
greatly increasing the number of sorties.

292
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:58,760
If Chiang Kai-shek's plot succeeds,

293
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,340
the damage to Shanghai

294
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,670
and New China

295
00:16:03,790 --> 00:16:05,120
would be unimaginable.

296
00:16:07,050 --> 00:16:08,550
The Nationalist Government
just used the Gold Yuan notes

297
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:10,240
to swindle people of their money.

298
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,100
They have fled,

299
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:13,440
and now they're turning back
to bomb their own people.

300
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,240
No wonder they're losing power.

301
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:17,880
Shanghai is just one part of it.

302
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:19,580
If they take this opportunity

303
00:16:19,580 --> 00:16:21,440
to fortify the Zhoushan Islands,

304
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:24,420
using the airports
and naval bases on the islands,

305
00:16:24,580 --> 00:16:26,840
they can not only
directly threaten East China,

306
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:27,550
but also

307
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,390
greatly affect the development

308
00:16:31,550 --> 00:16:33,680
of all cities along the Yangtze River.

309
00:16:39,930 --> 00:16:41,390
The urgent task now is to determine

310
00:16:41,210 --> 00:16:43,590
[D-Day: the day on which
a military operation begins]

311
00:16:41,390 --> 00:16:42,520
the D-Day timeframe

312
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:45,430
and send out the intelligence,

313
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:47,000
so that Shanghai

314
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,860
can prepare defenses in advance.

315
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:49,790
Sir,

316
00:16:50,630 --> 00:16:52,090
do you have any good ideas?

317
00:16:52,390 --> 00:16:53,200
Large-scale bombing

318
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:55,460
requires specific weather conditions.

319
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:00,480
The weather in Shanghai
and Zhoushan is similar.

320
00:17:00,890 --> 00:17:01,820
I need to know

321
00:17:01,820 --> 00:17:03,600
the weather conditions in Zhoushan waters.

322
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,599
Given the current level of secrecy,

323
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:08,109
trying to access weather reports

324
00:17:08,109 --> 00:17:09,710
from the meteorological station

325
00:17:09,710 --> 00:17:11,690
won't be easy.

326
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:13,960
Of course it won't be easy,

327
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:15,839
but we still need to try.

328
00:17:17,819 --> 00:17:19,680
Is Mrs. Chen's exit permit ready?

329
00:17:20,050 --> 00:17:20,810
It's ready.

330
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,589
I'll contact her first thing tomorrow.

331
00:17:22,589 --> 00:17:24,319
Ask her to pass a message to Wan,

332
00:17:25,290 --> 00:17:26,619
telling them to quickly

333
00:17:26,829 --> 00:17:29,250
send an experienced new courier here.

334
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:30,630
Understood.

335
00:17:38,130 --> 00:17:40,690
Hongxiang Silk Shop.
Is this Mrs. Chen speaking?

336
00:17:40,690 --> 00:17:41,420
Yes, it's me.

337
00:17:41,740 --> 00:17:43,940
The new fabric you ordered has arrived.

338
00:17:45,670 --> 00:17:47,800
Alright, I understand. Thank you.

339
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:07,610
Director Duan has become suspicious

340
00:18:07,610 --> 00:18:09,280
about our rendezvous
at the Power Company Guesthouse.

341
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:11,440
[Special pass]

342
00:18:09,690 --> 00:18:11,890
There's a flight to Zhoushan tomorrow.

343
00:18:12,110 --> 00:18:14,380
Comrade East Sea
has arranged a seat for you.

344
00:18:14,380 --> 00:18:15,270
To be safe,

345
00:18:15,830 --> 00:18:17,890
you should leave as soon as possible.

346
00:18:30,380 --> 00:18:31,810
I've thought it through.

347
00:18:32,610 --> 00:18:35,070
There are many comrades building Shanghai,

348
00:18:35,130 --> 00:18:36,520
but I'm the only one

349
00:18:36,540 --> 00:18:38,430
with a legal special pass.

350
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:42,210
This mission is my bounden duty.

351
00:18:43,220 --> 00:18:45,480
I wish you a swift and successful return.

352
00:18:45,770 --> 00:18:48,050
A man should stride boldly through life.

353
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:51,960
Can a woman not also be as mighty
as a whale crossing the sea?

354
00:19:23,460 --> 00:19:24,830
Hello, whom would you like to speak to?

355
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:27,280
Hello, may I speak to Yin Xuefen, please?

356
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:28,030
Yin Xuefen?

357
00:19:28,060 --> 00:19:29,320
I'm her old classmate.

358
00:19:30,090 --> 00:19:31,640
You mean Mrs. Lv, right?

359
00:19:32,050 --> 00:19:33,350
Her husband got promoted

360
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:34,750
and they no longer live here.

361
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:36,480
They moved out just last month.

362
00:19:37,270 --> 00:19:39,170
Do you know where they moved to?

363
00:19:39,590 --> 00:19:40,850
I really don't know.

364
00:19:41,860 --> 00:19:43,860
I'm sorry to have bothered you then.

365
00:19:46,940 --> 00:19:47,480
Mom.

366
00:19:48,290 --> 00:19:49,830
Who were you talking to on the phone?

367
00:19:49,830 --> 00:19:51,900
An old classmate
from when I was in Ningbo.

368
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:53,500
I heard she's also in Taipei.

369
00:19:53,610 --> 00:19:54,850
I wanted to get in touch with her.

370
00:19:54,850 --> 00:19:56,510
We were quite close back then.

371
00:19:56,510 --> 00:19:57,510
Did you reach her?

372
00:19:57,850 --> 00:19:58,980
They said she moved.

373
00:20:00,070 --> 00:20:01,890
Taipei may not be big,

374
00:20:01,970 --> 00:20:04,770
but finding someone
can still be quite difficult.

375
00:20:05,220 --> 00:20:06,400
Mom, you must be hungry.

376
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,940
Guess what I made for you?

377
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:09,630
What did you make?

378
00:20:09,630 --> 00:20:11,400
Sliced Pork with Pickled Cabbage.

379
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,490
Sounds wonderful.

380
00:20:12,630 --> 00:20:14,830
It's a specialty from Northeast China.

381
00:20:14,850 --> 00:20:16,100
I love it so much.

382
00:20:16,850 --> 00:20:17,980
Old habits die hard.

383
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:20,130
You're a product of where you're from.

384
00:20:20,530 --> 00:20:21,880
When I first came to Taipei,

385
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:23,760
I wanted to eat Sliced Pork
with Pickled Cabbage for every meal.

386
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:26,080
But there aren't many authentic
Northeast restaurants in Taipei,

387
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:27,070
and they're expensive too.

388
00:20:27,070 --> 00:20:29,000
I had to pickle the cabbage myself.

389
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:30,890
Ju.

390
00:20:31,620 --> 00:20:34,350
Are there any good
Ningbo restaurants in Taipei?

391
00:20:40,290 --> 00:20:40,880
Hello.

392
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:41,780
Please come in.

393
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:47,410
I've been looking for
your restaurant for a long time.

394
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,050
My usual three dishes:

395
00:21:23,050 --> 00:21:25,790
meatball soup,
pickled water bamboo, and smoked fish.

396
00:21:25,790 --> 00:21:26,570
Mrs. Chen,

397
00:21:26,570 --> 00:21:29,230
I'll throw in a serving
of rice cake on the house.

398
00:21:29,730 --> 00:21:30,860
That's too kind.

399
00:21:31,550 --> 00:21:32,440
It's our pleasure.

400
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:35,240
You've been patronizing us
for several days in a row.

401
00:21:35,240 --> 00:21:36,050
Thank you.

402
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,180
Our chefs

403
00:21:38,180 --> 00:21:39,740
are all from Zhenhai.

404
00:21:39,740 --> 00:21:41,480
I can't guarantee anything else,

405
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:43,680
but the taste is definitely authentic.

406
00:21:44,370 --> 00:21:46,390
Please wait a moment
while I prepare your order.

407
00:21:46,390 --> 00:21:46,990
Thank you.

408
00:22:00,330 --> 00:22:01,000
Mrs. Lv.

409
00:22:01,830 --> 00:22:02,790
Hello, Mr. Yu.

410
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:06,660
Yin Xuefen.

411
00:22:12,610 --> 00:22:13,590
Zhu Yi...

412
00:22:13,590 --> 00:22:14,570
Zhu Yiyin!

413
00:22:15,270 --> 00:22:16,630
What are you doing here?

414
00:22:17,010 --> 00:22:18,410
I came to see my daughter.

415
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:20,180
So you've come to Taipei too.

416
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:20,960
Yes.

417
00:22:22,130 --> 00:22:23,510
You haven't changed at all.

418
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:25,110
I recognized you right away.

419
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:25,830
Let me tell you.

420
00:22:25,830 --> 00:22:27,750
I've been waiting
for you here for 3 days.

421
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:29,810
You've been waiting for me for 3 days?

422
00:22:30,030 --> 00:22:31,810
Yes, before I came to Taiwan,

423
00:22:31,810 --> 00:22:33,270
they told me you were here.

424
00:22:33,350 --> 00:22:35,030
I thought I really had to see you.

425
00:22:35,030 --> 00:22:37,720
Then I called your home
and they said you'd moved.

426
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:38,610
So I thought,

427
00:22:38,610 --> 00:22:40,030
since you love food so much,

428
00:22:40,030 --> 00:22:42,390
and this Ningbo restaurant
is the best one here,

429
00:22:42,390 --> 00:22:44,030
I would definitely run into you.

430
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:45,900
And look, I finally found you!

431
00:22:46,110 --> 00:22:47,640
What if I hadn't come today?

432
00:22:47,940 --> 00:22:49,530
Then I would have kept waiting for you.

433
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:50,930
I would have waited forever.

434
00:22:50,930 --> 00:22:52,600
Until I finally saw you.

435
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:54,440
Well, you've found me today.

436
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:55,070
Let me treat you.

437
00:22:55,070 --> 00:22:55,830
Please sit.

438
00:22:56,350 --> 00:22:57,220
What are you treating me for?

439
00:22:57,220 --> 00:22:58,180
I've already ordered.

440
00:22:58,180 --> 00:23:00,360
Why don't you just add a few more dishes?

441
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:01,380
All right then.

442
00:23:01,410 --> 00:23:02,810
Mr. Yu, bring us the menu.

443
00:23:02,810 --> 00:23:03,320
Sure.

444
00:23:08,010 --> 00:23:09,590
These past few months in Taiwan,

445
00:23:09,590 --> 00:23:11,590
I still haven't been able to adjust.

446
00:23:11,830 --> 00:23:14,740
I keep thinking about
friends and family in Zhenhai.

447
00:23:14,740 --> 00:23:16,000
Sometimes in my heart,

448
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,270
I feel so empty.

449
00:23:17,380 --> 00:23:19,090
Fortunately, this restaurant

450
00:23:19,090 --> 00:23:20,850
serves very authentic food.

451
00:23:21,350 --> 00:23:23,740
It's completely
because of these familiar flavors

452
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:25,350
that I can bear staying here.

453
00:23:25,350 --> 00:23:26,110
Thank you.

454
00:23:26,620 --> 00:23:27,260
Thanks.

455
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:30,360
But from what I can see,

456
00:23:30,750 --> 00:23:32,410
your life seems quite lively.

457
00:23:33,070 --> 00:23:35,000
I saw you in the newspaper,

458
00:23:35,170 --> 00:23:36,460
with a group of ladies,

459
00:23:36,620 --> 00:23:38,370
doing some kind of charity sale

460
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:41,140
to support the troops
and civilians in Zhoushan, right?

461
00:23:41,140 --> 00:23:44,070
That event you mentioned
was organized by Mrs. Zhou.

462
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:46,660
She just wanted
to have a festive celebration.

463
00:23:46,660 --> 00:23:48,180
Actually, the charity sale

464
00:23:48,180 --> 00:23:49,240
was just an excuse.

465
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:51,700
But Xuefen,

466
00:23:52,020 --> 00:23:53,630
among all those ladies,

467
00:23:53,790 --> 00:23:55,920
you looked
the most beautiful in the photos.

468
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:56,990
Oh, not at all.

469
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,570
Actually, those ladies

470
00:23:58,570 --> 00:23:59,620
really are quite influential.

471
00:23:59,620 --> 00:24:00,730
What do you mean?

472
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:03,380
They are the wives of several generals

473
00:24:03,380 --> 00:24:05,130
from the Southeast
Military and Political Office,

474
00:24:05,130 --> 00:24:06,790
as well as the wives of the Deputy Chiefs

475
00:24:06,790 --> 00:24:09,120
and Directors of the Ministry of Defense.

476
00:24:11,380 --> 00:24:12,590
Do you meet often?

477
00:24:12,740 --> 00:24:15,300
About 2 or 3 times a week.

478
00:24:15,510 --> 00:24:16,930
Sometimes we play mahjong,

479
00:24:16,930 --> 00:24:18,330
sometimes we sing opera.

480
00:24:19,510 --> 00:24:22,290
Sounds very lively and fun.

481
00:24:22,570 --> 00:24:24,250
It is quite lively.

482
00:24:26,010 --> 00:24:26,900
Zhu Yiyin.

483
00:24:27,740 --> 00:24:29,140
I think you've changed.

484
00:24:30,330 --> 00:24:31,750
In the past,

485
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:32,900
you didn't seem to care much

486
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:34,700
about other people's business.

487
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:36,980
To be honest,

488
00:24:37,490 --> 00:24:38,820
since coming to Taiwan,

489
00:24:39,940 --> 00:24:41,170
where I know no one,

490
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,150
sometimes...

491
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:44,650
I'm feeling a bit bored too.

492
00:24:44,850 --> 00:24:46,610
So hearing about all your exciting stories

493
00:24:46,610 --> 00:24:47,500
makes me happy.

494
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:50,580
Actually, I heard that you

495
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:52,720
got married and moved to Shenyang,

496
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:55,790
and that your husband was an engineer.

497
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:58,420
He's my late husband now.

498
00:25:00,070 --> 00:25:01,270
His surname was Chen.

499
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,200
He was very good to me.

500
00:25:05,030 --> 00:25:05,900
I'm so sorry.

501
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,100
It's alright.

502
00:25:07,250 --> 00:25:08,380
It's all in the past.

503
00:25:08,670 --> 00:25:10,140
I've changed my name now.

504
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:12,210
I'm called Zhu Chenzhi.

505
00:25:12,220 --> 00:25:14,220
Mr. Sha Menghai helped me choose it.

506
00:25:15,190 --> 00:25:17,050
Zhu Chenzhi. That sounds lovely.

507
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:20,710
Mrs. Dou is organizing something tomorrow.

508
00:25:20,710 --> 00:25:22,170
Why don't you come with me?

509
00:25:22,350 --> 00:25:23,090
That won't do.

510
00:25:23,090 --> 00:25:24,640
I'm just an ordinary person.

511
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:26,380
How could I possibly
mingle with your crowd?

512
00:25:26,380 --> 00:25:27,640
What does that matter?

513
00:25:27,740 --> 00:25:29,460
You're my friend. Why shouldn't you?

514
00:25:29,460 --> 00:25:30,720
It's no problem at all.

515
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:33,750
It would be nice
to join in your lively gatherings.

516
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:35,900
So many ladies there.

517
00:25:36,220 --> 00:25:38,750
Is there any special
etiquette I should know?

518
00:25:51,500 --> 00:25:52,740
Looks like Mrs. Wu is here,

519
00:25:52,740 --> 00:25:53,480
isn't it?

520
00:25:53,700 --> 00:25:54,750
Juan, come here,

521
00:25:54,750 --> 00:25:55,880
draw for me.

522
00:25:56,740 --> 00:25:57,510
Hurry up.

523
00:25:58,270 --> 00:25:59,400
I have a great hand.

524
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,660
Keep an eye on it for me.

525
00:26:02,290 --> 00:26:04,190
I'm so sorry.

526
00:26:04,310 --> 00:26:05,420
Mrs. Lv,

527
00:26:05,570 --> 00:26:06,850
why are you so late?

528
00:26:06,850 --> 00:26:07,660
Didn't we agree

529
00:26:07,660 --> 00:26:09,400
you'd come for afternoon tea?

530
00:26:09,590 --> 00:26:10,790
I've spent my entire afternoon

531
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:12,390
entertaining my old friend.

532
00:26:12,990 --> 00:26:14,510
I should have called you.

533
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:15,590
That's right.

534
00:26:15,930 --> 00:26:17,130
Let me introduce you.

535
00:26:17,750 --> 00:26:18,500
Mrs. Chen,

536
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:20,820
my best friend from Ningbo.

537
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:22,830
Mrs. Dou,

538
00:26:23,140 --> 00:26:24,600
the one I told you about...

539
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,930
-...the star of Taipei's ladies' circle.
-The star.

540
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:30,790
Xuefen always mentions your name.

541
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:32,850
I finally meet you in person today.

542
00:26:33,210 --> 00:26:34,430
Mrs. Chen, right?

543
00:26:35,020 --> 00:26:36,940
Pleased to meet you. Please come in.

544
00:26:36,940 --> 00:26:37,700
Thank you.

545
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:40,630
Mrs. Chen just arrived from Hong Kong.

546
00:26:40,990 --> 00:26:43,590
I only got in touch
with her these past few days.

547
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:45,570
You know how it is — old friends meet

548
00:26:45,590 --> 00:26:47,190
and just can't stop talking.

549
00:26:47,480 --> 00:26:48,940
I brought her today

550
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:50,980
to meet some new friends.

551
00:26:53,330 --> 00:26:54,140
Liu,

552
00:26:54,660 --> 00:26:55,660
prepare some tea.

553
00:26:56,210 --> 00:26:56,970
Mrs. Dou,

554
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,580
I have a small gift for you.

555
00:26:59,380 --> 00:27:00,840
I bought this in Hong Kong.

556
00:27:00,990 --> 00:27:02,140
It's an American brand,

557
00:27:02,140 --> 00:27:03,220
quite a good one.

558
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:04,440
Just a small token.

559
00:27:05,460 --> 00:27:06,740
I know this one.

560
00:27:10,220 --> 00:27:11,160
This is America's

561
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:13,360
most popular style and color this year.

562
00:27:14,220 --> 00:27:15,960
Yes, exactly this color.

563
00:27:15,960 --> 00:27:18,620
I was asking someone
to bring me one from the U.S.

564
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:20,510
Juan, look,

565
00:27:20,540 --> 00:27:23,220
the one I had someone
bring from the U.S. is this exact color.

566
00:27:23,220 --> 00:27:24,070
This is beautiful.

567
00:27:24,070 --> 00:27:26,070
This brand is very famous in the U.S.

568
00:27:26,420 --> 00:27:27,880
No, no, this is too expensive.

569
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:28,900
How could I accept it?

570
00:27:28,900 --> 00:27:29,440
Please.

571
00:27:30,070 --> 00:27:31,160
Just accept it.

572
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:32,830
She does big business

573
00:27:32,830 --> 00:27:34,160
in Hong Kong.

574
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:36,140
She has plenty of American goods at home.

575
00:27:36,140 --> 00:27:37,160
Not at all.

576
00:27:37,610 --> 00:27:38,700
I'm glad you like it.

577
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:40,140
Just a small gesture.

578
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:09,530
Mrs. Wu, you're finally here!

579
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:11,520
I thought you weren't coming.

580
00:28:11,550 --> 00:28:12,610
How could I miss it?

581
00:28:12,620 --> 00:28:14,220
I just got delayed on the way.

582
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:16,430
Come in, let's talk inside.

583
00:28:16,660 --> 00:28:17,800
Let me tell you.

584
00:28:17,820 --> 00:28:19,140
Mrs. Duan

585
00:28:19,170 --> 00:28:20,910
wanted to come today.

586
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:22,680
She went too far last time,

587
00:28:22,700 --> 00:28:25,000
so I turned her down.

588
00:28:25,030 --> 00:28:27,140
I figured you wouldn't
want to see her either.

589
00:28:27,140 --> 00:28:28,130
I think

590
00:28:28,150 --> 00:28:30,480
she'll never come to Dou's Mansion again.

591
00:28:31,590 --> 00:28:33,860
It's so much nicer
to just play mahjong and sing.

592
00:28:33,860 --> 00:28:35,520
All that gossip is pointless.

593
00:28:35,670 --> 00:28:36,480
Exactly!

594
00:28:36,510 --> 00:28:38,170
This has nothing to do with me,

595
00:28:38,570 --> 00:28:40,570
or I'd truly be wrongfully accused.

596
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:43,430
You're not wearing enough.

597
00:28:43,450 --> 00:28:45,450
It wasn't this cold when I left home.

598
00:28:46,970 --> 00:28:48,830
Quite a crowd today, isn't there?

599
00:28:49,980 --> 00:28:51,550
Many experts have come today.

600
00:28:51,550 --> 00:28:52,180
Later,

601
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:53,930
we can have a good match together.

602
00:28:53,930 --> 00:28:54,560
Let's go.

603
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:01,060
That's Deputy Chief Wu's
wife, Wang Bikui.

604
00:29:01,060 --> 00:29:02,520
She's a valued guest here.

605
00:29:03,180 --> 00:29:04,630
She looks very kind.

606
00:29:04,660 --> 00:29:05,810
Sorry, I'm late.

607
00:29:05,810 --> 00:29:06,270
Would you like to play?

608
00:29:06,270 --> 00:29:08,920
You go ahead.

609
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:09,480
Don't let me interrupt.

610
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,780
Alright, carry on chatting.

611
00:29:10,780 --> 00:29:13,060
We have a new friend today, Mrs. Chen,

612
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:14,450
who is Mrs. Lv's friend.

613
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:16,400
She just arrived from Hong Kong.

614
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:17,640
Yes, Mrs. Chen

615
00:29:17,640 --> 00:29:19,200
is here for the first time today.

616
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:20,060
Hello, Mrs. Wu.

617
00:29:20,100 --> 00:29:21,090
Hello, Mrs. Chen.

618
00:29:21,090 --> 00:29:21,880
Pleased to meet you.

619
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:22,510
Likewise.

620
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:27,540
The secret bombing plan alerted Wu Shi

621
00:29:28,030 --> 00:29:30,760
that Chiang Kai-shek
might already suspect him.

622
00:29:31,370 --> 00:29:33,900
He carefully reviewed
his previous actions,

623
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:36,640
trying to determine if he was overthinking

624
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:38,680
or if he had overlooked something.

625
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:41,570
Every step forward

626
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:44,470
would require extreme caution.

627
00:29:48,590 --> 00:29:55,610
♪ While no one is around ♪

628
00:29:56,400 --> 00:30:14,220
♪ It's the perfect time
to drift into a dream ♪

629
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:21,090
Mrs. Lv.

630
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:23,050
Your singing has improved so much.

631
00:30:23,090 --> 00:30:25,200
I was completely enchanted.

632
00:30:25,220 --> 00:30:26,660
You're too kind.

633
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:30,190
Now that I've finished
"The Search for the Dream",

634
00:30:30,190 --> 00:30:32,320
who will sing "A Stroll in the Garden"?

635
00:30:34,070 --> 00:30:34,900
Mrs. Wu.

636
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:37,130
Weren't you going to sing a few pieces?

637
00:30:37,250 --> 00:30:39,410
How about singing
"A Stroll in the Garden"?

638
00:30:39,410 --> 00:30:40,030
Yes, indeed.

639
00:30:40,030 --> 00:30:41,030
Sing one, Mrs. Wu.

640
00:30:41,030 --> 00:30:42,630
I just had a couple of drinks,

641
00:30:42,690 --> 00:30:44,380
and my voice isn't cooperating.

642
00:30:44,380 --> 00:30:45,090
Please continue without me.

643
00:30:45,090 --> 00:30:46,240
I don't want to spoil the fun.

644
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:47,890
Just sing a verse.

645
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:49,810
Your voice is so beautiful.

646
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:50,790
Yes.

647
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:51,750
You sing so well.

648
00:30:51,750 --> 00:30:53,140
Please do sing.

649
00:30:53,140 --> 00:30:55,720
How about I give it a humble try?

650
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:57,190
Great!

651
00:30:57,220 --> 00:30:58,390
Wonderful!

652
00:30:58,410 --> 00:30:59,250
Excellent!

653
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:00,280
May I borrow your fan?

654
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:00,840
Good.

655
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:02,020
Play the music.

656
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:10,620
♪ Without stepping into the garden ♪

657
00:31:11,020 --> 00:31:23,610
♪ How could one ever know
such splendor of spring? ♪

658
00:31:23,730 --> 00:31:25,050
Wonderful!

659
00:31:34,610 --> 00:31:35,810
Welcome back, Mr. Wu.

660
00:31:43,800 --> 00:31:46,030
Have you had dinner, sir?

661
00:31:46,860 --> 00:31:47,660
Yes, I have.

662
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:50,100
Mrs. Wu isn't home.

663
00:31:50,130 --> 00:31:52,360
She went to Dou's Mansion to play mahjong.

664
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:55,490
The young master
and the young lady have both gone to bed.

665
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:12,070
♪ Though the peony is fair ♪

666
00:32:13,860 --> 00:32:25,960
♪ How could it claim
the first grace of spring's return? ♪

667
00:32:26,100 --> 00:32:39,730
♪ Pausing idly, I gaze ♪

668
00:32:39,910 --> 00:32:58,250
♪ The swallows' bright chatter
cuts the air like scissors ♪

669
00:32:58,340 --> 00:33:05,730
♪ And listen—the orioles trill,
their notes round and clear ♪

670
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:07,990
That was beautiful!

671
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:12,340
You two sing together so well.

672
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:14,750
I'm so happy. Thank you.

673
00:33:15,150 --> 00:33:17,150
It's a pleasure to meet you all.

674
00:33:19,070 --> 00:33:20,380
Here, have some fruit.

675
00:33:28,700 --> 00:33:30,890
Mrs. Wu, your voice is wonderful.

676
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:34,320
You can hit the high notes
and reach the low ones too.

677
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:35,980
It sounds so fluid and natural.

678
00:33:35,980 --> 00:33:37,140
So graceful and elegant.

679
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:38,160
You're too kind.

680
00:33:38,390 --> 00:33:39,640
Mrs. Chen, you flatter me.

681
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:40,570
I really mean it.

682
00:33:40,940 --> 00:33:42,920
When I heard you sing, I thought

683
00:33:43,390 --> 00:33:45,050
it was absolutely beautiful.

684
00:33:45,140 --> 00:33:46,740
Why didn't you sing earlier?

685
00:33:47,980 --> 00:33:49,510
There were too many people.

686
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:50,960
I was too shy to sing.

687
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:54,390
Mrs. Wu, you seem quite introverted.

688
00:33:55,510 --> 00:33:57,100
Mrs. Dou is very lively.

689
00:33:57,790 --> 00:33:59,190
And very hospitable too.

690
00:33:59,550 --> 00:34:02,080
She enjoys
being around people, doesn't she?

691
00:34:02,850 --> 00:34:05,180
Mrs. Chen, you're here for the first time,

692
00:34:05,780 --> 00:34:08,510
yet you seem quite comfortable,
not nervous at all.

693
00:34:08,510 --> 00:34:10,370
I'm quite alright in that regard.

694
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:12,030
I do business in Hong Kong.

695
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:14,639
I'm used to meeting all sorts of people.

696
00:34:15,300 --> 00:34:16,960
Where are you from, Mrs. Chen?

697
00:34:17,300 --> 00:34:18,760
I'm from Zhenhai, Ningbo.

698
00:34:20,679 --> 00:34:23,219
Are you in Taiwan for business?

699
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:27,030
No, I'm here to visit my daughter.

700
00:34:27,489 --> 00:34:28,510
She had a baby.

701
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:30,000
A little one.

702
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:32,310
You're so young.

703
00:34:32,340 --> 00:34:34,000
Are you really a grandmother?

704
00:34:34,210 --> 00:34:35,600
I'm not young at all.

705
00:34:35,630 --> 00:34:36,900
You're too kind.

706
00:34:37,570 --> 00:34:38,969
You really do look young.

707
00:34:40,719 --> 00:34:43,010
Before doing business in Hong Kong,

708
00:34:43,030 --> 00:34:44,090
I was in Shanghai.

709
00:34:44,690 --> 00:34:46,130
I've run a money shop

710
00:34:46,550 --> 00:34:47,750
and also a bookstore.

711
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:51,040
I've done a bit

712
00:34:51,070 --> 00:34:52,530
of every kind of business.

713
00:34:54,070 --> 00:34:55,199
That's impressive,

714
00:34:55,199 --> 00:34:57,330
to have done so many different things.

715
00:34:58,030 --> 00:34:59,500
I've been to Shanghai too.

716
00:34:59,820 --> 00:35:01,430
My daughter studies there.

717
00:35:01,820 --> 00:35:03,550
I think it's a wonderful place.

718
00:35:03,880 --> 00:35:06,010
My daughter also studies in Shanghai.

719
00:35:06,340 --> 00:35:08,130
My daughter studies medicine.

720
00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:09,270
Really?

721
00:35:09,980 --> 00:35:12,000
My daughter studies medicine too.

722
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:13,370
Really?

723
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:14,990
What a coincidence!

724
00:35:19,010 --> 00:35:20,680
Mrs. Wu, what's your name?

725
00:35:22,030 --> 00:35:23,780
I mean your maiden name.

726
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:27,470
Bikui.

727
00:35:27,890 --> 00:35:29,020
Wang Bikui.

728
00:35:29,470 --> 00:35:30,590
Wang Bikui.

729
00:35:31,290 --> 00:35:33,230
I'm Zhu. Zhu Chenzhi.

730
00:35:35,420 --> 00:35:36,920
It's been so long since anyone

731
00:35:36,920 --> 00:35:38,450
has asked me my maiden name.

732
00:35:39,590 --> 00:35:40,880
Usually,

733
00:35:41,090 --> 00:35:43,930
it's only because of the title "Mrs. Wu"

734
00:35:44,510 --> 00:35:46,780
that I'm treated as a valued guest here.

735
00:35:50,750 --> 00:35:52,210
This Mrs. and that Mrs.,

736
00:35:52,240 --> 00:35:53,990
it just sounds more formal.

737
00:35:55,390 --> 00:35:57,890
Using maiden names
feels more intimate, doesn't it?

738
00:35:57,890 --> 00:35:58,720
Yes.

739
00:35:59,450 --> 00:36:01,920
I've grown used to being called "Mother"

740
00:36:01,940 --> 00:36:03,360
or "Mrs." in my daily life.

741
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:06,090
It's been so long
that I've forgotten my own name.

742
00:36:07,590 --> 00:36:08,360
But I think

743
00:36:09,350 --> 00:36:11,390
being a mother has its own pride.

744
00:36:12,650 --> 00:36:15,190
I have two of my children here,
and they're both very well-behaved.

745
00:36:15,190 --> 00:36:18,270
My husband is
very responsible about their education.

746
00:36:19,340 --> 00:36:22,100
But I still have two grown children
in mainland China.

747
00:36:22,100 --> 00:36:24,150
They're out of sight and out of reach.

748
00:36:24,150 --> 00:36:25,590
Even if they get sick,

749
00:36:25,590 --> 00:36:27,150
I can't take care of them.

750
00:36:28,050 --> 00:36:29,250
Thinking about this,

751
00:36:29,900 --> 00:36:31,380
I feel quite guilty.

752
00:36:33,060 --> 00:36:34,420
For me, it's like this.

753
00:36:35,670 --> 00:36:37,400
When I'm at home,

754
00:36:37,610 --> 00:36:39,000
I often think

755
00:36:39,150 --> 00:36:40,950
I should go out and do something.

756
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:43,800
But when I actually go out,

757
00:36:44,860 --> 00:36:46,170
I often think

758
00:36:47,230 --> 00:36:49,020
it's better to stay home with the children

759
00:36:49,020 --> 00:36:50,540
and my husband.

760
00:36:52,690 --> 00:36:54,900
People are always
contradicting themselves.

761
00:36:54,900 --> 00:36:55,710
So sometimes

762
00:36:55,710 --> 00:36:57,370
you have to cheer yourself up.

763
00:36:57,670 --> 00:36:59,800
I'm happy to be at Dou's Mansion today.

764
00:37:00,100 --> 00:37:01,850
We drink tea, chat,

765
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:03,280
and sing opera together.

766
00:37:04,110 --> 00:37:05,260
It's really lively.

767
00:37:07,420 --> 00:37:09,950
Would you like to go in
and sing another piece?

768
00:37:10,470 --> 00:37:11,680
I'll stay here a bit longer.

769
00:37:11,680 --> 00:37:13,980
I feel sitting here chatting with you

770
00:37:14,570 --> 00:37:16,260
is more comfortable than being inside.

771
00:37:16,260 --> 00:37:18,630
Remember you promised
to visit my home in a few days.

772
00:37:18,630 --> 00:37:20,030
I'll bake some pastries for you.

773
00:37:20,030 --> 00:37:22,660
Sure, I'll definitely come visit.

774
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:23,440
Great.

775
00:37:24,610 --> 00:37:26,670
Mrs. Dou, thank you so much for today.

776
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:28,330
For your warm hospitality.

777
00:37:28,610 --> 00:37:30,110
Mrs. Chen, you're too kind.

778
00:37:30,110 --> 00:37:32,040
I was worried I wasn't being a good host.

779
00:37:32,040 --> 00:37:32,730
Not at all.

780
00:37:33,150 --> 00:37:35,420
Mrs. Chen, you must come visit more often.

781
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:37,570
Mrs. Wu rarely gets
along with people so well.

782
00:37:37,570 --> 00:37:38,570
Sure, I'd love to.

783
00:37:40,530 --> 00:37:41,420
Take care on your way.

784
00:37:41,420 --> 00:37:42,320
Okay.

785
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:42,960
I'll be going now.

786
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:43,840
Goodbye.

787
00:37:44,010 --> 00:37:45,210
Great, we'll visit often.

788
00:37:45,210 --> 00:37:45,920
See you later.

789
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:47,440
Come together. Goodbye.

790
00:37:53,300 --> 00:37:54,710
What brings

791
00:37:54,710 --> 00:37:57,130
our busy Director Duan here today?

792
00:37:58,040 --> 00:38:00,100
Mrs. Dou, you're still so beautiful.

793
00:38:00,230 --> 00:38:00,810
You flatter me.

794
00:38:00,810 --> 00:38:02,480
I'm here to pick up my darling.

795
00:38:04,090 --> 00:38:05,090
She's not here.

796
00:38:06,070 --> 00:38:07,330
She didn't come today.

797
00:38:08,270 --> 00:38:09,630
She hasn't been here today.

798
00:38:09,630 --> 00:38:10,040
But wait.

799
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:13,300
She told me she's been
hanging out at your place these days.

800
00:38:13,540 --> 00:38:16,740
She told you she's been
hanging out at my place these days?

801
00:38:17,180 --> 00:38:18,720
I haven't seen her for ages.

802
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,370
Director Duan,

803
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:26,940
your wife is

804
00:38:26,970 --> 00:38:28,660
young and beautiful.

805
00:38:28,900 --> 00:38:30,650
And she has quite a free spirit.

806
00:38:31,350 --> 00:38:33,080
You'd better keep an eye on her.

807
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,570
I'll be going now.

808
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:50,360
Mrs. Wu, you're back.

809
00:39:39,050 --> 00:39:41,450
Honey. Why are you
in such a good mood today?

810
00:39:43,430 --> 00:39:44,770
I met a new friend

811
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:46,190
at Dou's Mansion today.

812
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:49,560
We were like old friends at first sight.

813
00:39:49,590 --> 00:39:51,490
I'm happy when I think of her.

814
00:39:51,690 --> 00:39:53,090
What's that friend like?

815
00:39:53,980 --> 00:39:56,020
I'll invite her to our home

816
00:39:56,210 --> 00:39:57,730
and introduce her to you.

817
00:39:58,250 --> 00:39:59,850
I'm sure you'll like her too.

818
00:39:59,890 --> 00:40:00,460
Alright.

819
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,200
I'm done singing.

820
00:40:02,750 --> 00:40:03,420
Let's go to bed.

821
00:40:03,420 --> 00:40:04,110
Honey.

822
00:40:04,910 --> 00:40:06,940
I'd like to hear you sing one more piece.

823
00:40:06,940 --> 00:40:08,540
You've heard me sing before.

824
00:40:10,620 --> 00:40:11,550
I want to hear it.

825
00:40:32,090 --> 00:41:03,590
♪ The sea moon,
pure as ice, begins its ascent ♪

826
00:41:03,590 --> 00:41:16,070
♪ The jade rabbit appears ♪

827
00:41:16,980 --> 00:41:30,360
♪ And soon ascends again from the east ♪

828
00:42:54,300 --> 00:42:55,760
Hold him down. Don't move.

829
00:42:56,020 --> 00:42:56,850
Let me go!

830
00:42:57,410 --> 00:42:58,870
You inspection soldiers!

831
00:42:59,050 --> 00:42:59,710
Don't move!

832
00:42:59,820 --> 00:43:00,590
Let me go!

833
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:02,580
Don't move!

834
00:43:02,920 --> 00:43:03,950
Let me go!

